etymologies: early 20th century. From scientific Latin Prunus, genus name (from classical Latin prūnus) + -etin

definitions: A colourless crystalline compound related to isoflavone which occurs in the wood and bark of several trees.

notes.text: Prunetin is the monomethyl ether of prunetol (genistein). Formula: C₁₆H₁₂O₅.
